qas.question: Who was the first woman MP to take her seat in the British Parliament?
For what constituency was Nancy Astor elected?
On what date did Plymouth become a city?
In what year did Plymouth receive its first Lord Mayor?
What parish was incorporated into Plymouth in 1967?

context: In 1919 <a0_0>Nancy Astor<a0_0/> was elected the first ever female member of parliament to take office in the British Houses of Parliament for the constituency of <a1_0>Plymouth Sutton<a1_0/>. Taking over office from her husband Waldorf Astor, Lady Astor was a vibrantly active campaigner for her resident constituents . Plymouth was granted city status on <a2_0>18 October 1928<a2_0/>. The city's first Lord Mayor was appointed in <a3_0>1935<a3_0/> and its boundaries further expanded in 1967 to include the town of Plympton and the parish of <a4_0>Plymstock<a4_0/>.
